"title": "1511: Trinity, relationships between the persons",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1511",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The actual term “the Trinity” is not found in Scripture, but the truths implied in a trinitarian understanding of God are clearly set out. The OT hints at a plurality of persons in the Godhead. The NT affirms that the Son and the Holy Spirit are divine.</p>\n<h2>There is only one God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:4\">DEU 6:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:10-Isa43:11\">ISA 43:10–43:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:8\">ISA 44:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:17\">1TI 1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:5\">1TI 2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:19\">JAS 2:19</a></p>\n<h2>OT indications of plurality in the Godhead</h2>\n<h3>God refers to himself in the plural</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:26\">GEN 1:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:22\">GEN 3:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen11:7\">GEN 11:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:8\">ISA 6:8</a></p>\n<h3>The angel of the LORD</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen16:11-Gen16:13\">GEN 16:11–16:13</a></strong> <em>The “angel of the LORD” is identified with, yet distinct from, God.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:1-Gen18:33\">GEN 18:1–18:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:2-Exod3:6\">EXO 3:2–3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg13:3-Judg13:22\">JDG 13:3–13:22</a></p>\n<h3>The word of God</h3>\n<p>The <code>word of the LORD'' or</code>wisdom of God'' is personified and identified with, yet distinct from, God:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:4\">PSA 33:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov8:22-Prov8:31\">PRO 8:22–8:31</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit of God</h3>\n<p>The Spirit of God is God's personal agent:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:2\">GEN 1:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:20\">NEH 9:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job33:4\">JOB 33:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:13\">ISA 40:13</a></p>\n<h3>The Messiah</h3>\n<p>The Messiah's divine nature is emphasised:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps110:1\">PSA 110:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:6\">ISA 9:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:5-Jer23:6\">JER 23:5–23:6</a></p>\n<h3>Interchangeable expressions</h3>\n<p>Word, Spirit (or breath) and LORD are used interchangeably for God:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:6\">PSA 33:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:16\">ISA 48:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1\">ISA 61:1</a></p>\n<h2>NT trinitarian references</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19\">MAT 28:19</a></strong> <em>The unity of the three persons is reflected in the singular name.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor13:14\">2CO 13:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:4-Eph4:6\">EPH 4:4–4:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:4-Rev1:5\">REV 1:4–1:5</a></p>\n<h2>The unity of the three persons</h2>\n<h3>The Son is fully united with the Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:30\">JHN 10:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:37\">MRK 9:37</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:48\">LUK 9:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:16\">LUK 10:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:38\">JHN 10:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:44-John12:45\">JHN 12:44–12:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:20\">JHN 13:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:7\">JHN 14:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:9-John14:11\">JHN 14:9–14:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:23\">JHN 15:23</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit is identified with God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:2-2Sam23:3\">2SA 23:2–23:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:11\">PSA 51:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19\">MAT 28:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:16\">1CO 3:16</a></p>\n<h2>The three persons are distinct from one another</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ addresses the Father directly</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:25-Matt11:26\">MAT 11:25–11:26</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:21\">LUK 10:21</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:39\">MAT 26:39</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:36\">MRK 14:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:42\">LUK 22:42</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:42\">MAT 26:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:46\">MAT 27:46</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:34\">MRK 15:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:46\">LUK 23:46</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:41-John11:42\">JHN 11:41–11:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:1\">JHN 17:1</a></p>\n<h3>The Father speaks to the Son from heaven</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt3:17\">MAT 3:17</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:11\">MRK 1:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:22\">LUK 3:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:5\">MAT 17:5</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:7\">MRK 9:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:35\">LUK 9:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:27-John12:28\">JHN 12:27–12:28</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit speaks to the Father on behalf of believers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:26-Rom8:27\">ROM 8:26–8:27</a></p>\n<h3>Other examples of the difference between the persons</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:32\">MAT 12:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:36\">MAT 24:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:39\">JHN 7:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:7\">JHN 16:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:5\">1TI 2:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:1\">1JN 2:1</a></p>\n<h2>The relationship between the Father and the Son</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is God's unique Son</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a></strong> <em>The Greek word for “One and Only”, traditionally rendered “only begotten”, is actually used to signify “the only one of its kind”; “unique”.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:18\">JHN 1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:16\">JHN 3:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:18\">JHN 3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:33\">ACT 13:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:5\">HEB 1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:7\">PSA 2:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:9\">1JN 4:9</a></p>\n<h3>The relationship of Father and Son is unique</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:27\">MAT 11:27</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:22\">LUK 10:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:46\">JHN 6:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:28-John7:29\">JHN 7:28–7:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:55\">JHN 8:55</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:15\">JHN 10:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:25\">JHN 17:25</a></p>\n<h3>The Father loves the Son</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:35\">JHN 3:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:20\">JHN 5:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:17\">JHN 10:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:9\">JHN 15:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:24\">JHN 17:24</a></p>\n<h3>The Father shares his divine life with the Son</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:9\">COL 2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:26\">JHN 5:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:57\">JHN 6:57</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:19\">COL 1:19</a></p>\n<h3>The Father delegates his authority to the Son</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:27\">JHN 5:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:18\">MAT 28:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:35\">JHN 3:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:21-John5:22\">JHN 5:21–5:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:15\">JHN 16:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:26-Rev2:27\">REV 2:26–2:27</a></p>\n<h3>Father and Son indwell each other</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:10-John14:11\">JHN 14:10–14:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:38\">JHN 10:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:20\">JHN 14:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:21-John17:23\">JHN 17:21–17:23</a></p>\n<h2>The relationship between the Holy Spirit and the other two persons</h2>\n<h3>The Spirit is <code>the Spirit of God'' and</code>the Spirit of Christ''</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:9\">ROM 8:9</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:33\">PSA 106:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:14\">1CO 2:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:3\">PHP 3:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:2\">1JN 4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:7\">ACT 16:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:6\">GAL 4:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:19\">PHP 1:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:11\">1PE 1:11</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit's unique relationship with God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:20\">MAT 10:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:10-1Cor2:11\">1CO 2:10–2:11</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit's unique relationship with the Son</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:33\">JHN 1:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1\">ISA 61:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:16-John14:17\">JHN 14:16–14:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:26\">JHN 14:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:38\">ACT 10:38</a></p>",
